Therefore, for Δ T → 0, ordinary MD is recovered, whereas the Δ T → ∞ limit corresponds to standard metadynamics. In between one can regulate the extent of FES exploration by tuning Δ T . This avoids overfilling and might save computational time when a large number of CVs are used. Figure 2 shows how the choice of Δ T affects the exploration and the convergence of the free-energy difference between two metastable states of alanine dipeptide.
